g.text: What its for: This is where you keep your vehicles healthy. It tracks every time a vehicle goes in for a check-up or a repair.

g.text: The "Auto-Hide" Rule: As soon as you add a vehicle to a maintenance log, the system automatically marks it as "In Shop."

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The Benefit: While a vehicle is "In Shop," the Dispatcher cannot see it or pick it for a new trip.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: This prevents you from accidentally sending a broken truck out on a delivery.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The Math: It adds up the fuel costs and the repair bills to show you the "Total Cost" for each vehicle. This helps you see if a specific truck is becoming too expensive to keep.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The "Safety Lock" Rule: If a drivers license expires, the system automatically locks them. You won't be able to assign them to any new trips until they renew it.
